.json
L6
Validation Schema
.schema.json
2. Canonical Prompt Artifact Schema (Human-Readable)
Every prompt file MUST conform to:
Copy code

/prompts/{Category}/OPRMT-{Category}-{Function}-vX.X.X.md
2.1 Markdown Structural Schema
Copy code

# OPRMT™ Prompt Title

## Metadata
ID:
Category:
Subcategory:
Version:
Status:
Author:
Created:
Updated:
License:
ComplianceScore:
DeterministicLevel:

---

## O — Objective
(1 deterministic objective only)

---

## P — Parameters
Role:
Constraints:
Assumptions:
InputVariables:

---

## R — Results
OutputFormat:
RequiredSections:
ValidationCriteria:

---

## M — Method
Step-by-step deterministic execution logic.

---

## T — Tools
RequiredTools:
OptionalTools:
AutomationHooks:
3. Machine-Readable Metadata Schema
Each prompt must optionally include:
Copy code

/metadata/{prompt-id}.json
3.1 Metadata JSON Structure
Copy code
Json
{
  "id": "OPRMT-Marketing-LeadGenScript-v1.0.0",
  "framework": "OPRMT",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "category": "Marketing",
  "subcategory": "LeadGeneration",
  "status": "stable",
  "author": "Michael W. Fleming",
  "license": "Custom-OPRMT-Free",
  "deterministic_level": 4,
  "compliance_score": 92,
  "created": "2026-02-11",
  "updated": "2026-02-11",
  "dependencies": [],
  "automation_ready": true
}
4. Taxonomy Registry Schema
Location:
Copy code

/taxonomy/taxonomy.json
4.1 Taxonomy JSON
Copy code
Json
{
  "categories": [
    {
      "name": "Marketing",
      "description": "Funnel, copy, campaign systems",
      "subcategories": [
        "LeadGeneration",
        "EmailCampaign",
        "ContentCalendar"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Business",
      "description": "Strategy and modeling systems",
      "subcategories": [
        "BusinessPlan",
        "MarketAnalysis",
        "Pricing"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "version": "1.0.0"
}
5. Compliance Scoring Schema
Location:
Copy code

/compliance/compliance-model.json
5.1 Compliance Model Structure
Copy code
Json
{
  "scoring_weights": {
    "objective_clarity": 20,
    "parameter_precision": 20,
    "result_structure": 20,
    "method_determinism": 20,
    "tool_specification": 10,
    "validation_criteria": 10
  },
  "max_score": 100,
  "passing_score": 85,
  "version": "1.0.0"
}
6. Repository Governance Schema
Location:
Copy code

/governance/governance.json
Copy code
Json
{
  "governance_model": "Centralized",
  "approval_authority": "Michael W. Fleming",
  "protected_branches": ["main"],
  "required_reviews": 1,
  "semantic_versioning": true,
  "release_commit_format": "RELEASE: vX.Y.Z",
  "version": "1.0.0"
}
7. JSON Schema for Validation (Automation Layer)
Location:
Copy code

/schemas/prompt.schema.json
7.1 Prompt Metadata Validation Schema
Copy code
Json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "OPRMT Prompt Metadata Schema",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "id",
    "framework",
    "version",
    "category",
    "status",
    "author",
    "license",
    "deterministic_level",
    "compliance_score"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^OPRMT-[A-Za-z]+-[A-Za-z]+-v\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$"
    },
    "framework": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["OPRMT"]
    },
    "version": {
      "type": "string",
      "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$"
    },
    "category": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "status": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["draft", "stable", "deprecated"]
    },
    "deterministic_level": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 1,
      "maximum": 5
    },
    "compliance_score": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 0,
      "maximum": 100
    }
  }
}
8. CI Validation Workflow (GitHub Actions Concept)
Workflow:
On PR
Validate:
Filename matches pattern
Metadata JSON validates against schema
Compliance score ≥ passing_score
Reject if:
Missing required fields
Version not incremented
Taxonomy mismatch
9. Deterministic Level Scale
Level
Definition
1
Creative prompt
2
Semi-structured
3
Structured
4
Deterministic
5
Fully auditable / automation-ready
Free Library minimum: Level 3
Preferred: Level 4+
10. Schema Version Control Strategy
Each schema file must include:
Copy code

"version": "X.Y.Z"
Schema changes require:
MINOR bump for additions
MAJOR bump for breaking structural changes
